  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All women had been amenorrheic for at least 1.5 year.

          -  Menopausal status was confirmed by a serum concentration of follicular- stimulating
             hormone (FSH &gt; 34 IU/ml) and estradiol (E2 &lt;50 pmol/l).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Cigarette smokers and women with:

               -  Hypertension

               -  Diabetes mellitus

               -  Clinical manifestations of arteriosclerosis (coronary heart disease, peripheral
                  artery disease, or cerebrovascular disease)

               -  Venous thromboembolic disease

               -  Liver disorders

               -  Unexplained vaginal bleeding; and

               -  Personal or family history of breast cancer were excluded.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
